    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "And... I got it figured out 10 minutes after posting this.\r\n\r\nI needed to include the autocomplete import like so:\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport { connectAutocomplete } from 'instantsearch.js/es/connectors';\r\n```\r\n\r\nThen I needed to call the renderAutocomplete like so:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst customAutocomplete = connectAutocomplete(\r\n  renderAutocomplete\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe docs currently show to use it like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nconst customAutocomplete = instantsearch.connectors.connectAutocomplete(\r\n  renderAutocomplete\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich was not working for me, so make sure to call `connectAutocomplete` by itself. Thought I would post my solution here in case anyone else ran into the same issue 👍 ",
